-------------------------------------------------5th Video--------------------------------------------------------------


how to set default values for package.json files

set the default author name - npm config set init-author-name "Tausif"
set the default license - npm % npm set init-license "TausifCG"


how to get default author name - npm config get init-author-name
how to get the default license -  npm get init-license

how to delete the default autor name we have set - npm config delete init-author-name
how to delete the default license we have set- npm config delete init-license

--------------------------------------------------6th Video--------------------------------------------------------------

How to install and add Dependency in Package.json file

only install library inthe file (moment is basically a javascript date library  )    - npm install moment

install and  add dependency  in package.json                            - npm install moment --save

required only for development purpose not for production then  -    npm install lodash --save-dev
this above will create another dependency called as devdepencies.


-----------------------------------------------------7th Video--------------------------------------------------------------

how to uninstall node modules from the file 

this will delete the module but not from the package.json -       npm uninstall moment

then to save to the package .json file then we have run   -       npm uninstall moment --save

then to remove the dev dependency from the package.json file -    npm uninstall lodash --save-dev

---------------------------------------------------8th Video------------------------------------------------------------

how to install dependency globally 

install the package globally just add the g    -   npm install moment -g


---------------------------------------------------9th Video------------------------------------------------------------

how to uninstall package ?

this command can be used to remove/uninstall the package -    npm uninstall moment -g

alias or another method you can uninstall the package 

npm uninstall
npm remove
npm rm
npm un
---------------------------------------------------10th Videos----------------------------------------------------------

How to listing Pcakage ?
only shows the list -       npm list
shows the 1 dependency -    npm list -depth 1
shows the 0 dependency-    npm list -depth 0
shows globally installed packages - npm list --global true --depth 0


